## Spring Boot

Q: What is Spring Boot?
Spring Boot is a framework used to build production-ready Spring applications quickly.

Q: Why Spring Boot?
It reduces configuration and provides auto-configuration.

Q: What is @SpringBootApplication?
It is the main annotation that starts Spring Boot app.

## REST

Q: What is REST API?
REST API is an API that uses HTTP methods like GET, POST, PUT, DELETE.

Q: What is @RestController?
It is used to create REST APIs that return JSON.

## JPA

Q: What is JPA?
JPA is a standard API to interact with database.

Q: What is Hibernate?
Hibernate is an implementation of JPA.

Q: What is ORM?
ORM maps Java objects to database tables.

## Spring Core

Q: What is Dependency Injection?
Spring creates and injects objects automatically.

Q: What is @Autowired?
It tells Spring to inject dependency.

## Exception & Validation

Q: How do you handle exception?
Using @ControllerAdvice and @ExceptionHandler.

Q: How do you validate input?
Using @Valid, @NotBlank, @Email.

## DTO & Pagination

Q: Why DTO?
To avoid exposing entity directly.

Q: What is pagination?
Loading data page by page.

## Swagger

Q: Why Swagger?
For API documentation and testing.

## Security

Q: What is Spring Security?
Used to protect APIs using authentication.

## AWS

Q: How did you deploy?
Using AWS EC2 and RDS conceptually.

## Java

Q: final vs finally vs finalize?
final = constant, finally = block, finalize = GC method.

Q: What is Optional?
Avoids NullPointerException.

Q: What is Stream?
Used for functional data processing.
